title: 35 MIN GENTLE PILATES || Full Body Workout (No Equipment)
description:
This 35 Minute Gentle Pilates Workout is perfect for those days when you need to slow things down and re-connect with your body and breath. This class is perfect for a morning or evening practice, moving the body gently but still providing an effective workout. 

🌸  Wearing Gymshark

channelDescription:
Hi, I'm Nicole! 😊 I am a Certified Pilates & Certified Yoga Instructor (RYT 500) with many years of in-studio teaching experience. As a former dancer and gymnast, I have always had a passion for movement and I love being able to share that passion with others. I believe in finding forms of movement that feel good for your body and soul and I hope that through my classes, I can guide you to your best feeling self!

--
I was a professional Latin Ballroom Dancer and taught Ballroom dancing to adults for 7+ years. This is truly where I established my passion for teaching movement. When I retired from competitive dancing in 2017, I began teaching Barre and Pilates in studios and gyms in Sydney.

During COVID lockdown, Dance & Pilates studios closed and that was when I poured my love of teaching into this channel, hoping to help people keep moving and feeling good!

Thank you so much for practicing with me and I hope you enjoy the classes as much as I love creating them for you. 🩷

comments: Like many others who commented, I did this workout after weeks of being too ill to exercise. (I’ve had cancer treatments.) It’s so good to have these wonderful gentle sessions on your channel, perfect for getting a tired and battered body back to moving again. Wouldn’t mind a few more of these... Thank you!
My hips, knees, and lower back were hurting before starting this workout. I feel 100% better after completing this. Thank you so much Nicole! 💚
Gentle Pilates.. whaaaattt??? I’m dying here, but as a beginner I’m very grateful for these workout videos! Thank you Nicole 💗

I did this exercise because I’m in the hospital for depression and anxiety and my doctor said I could do Pilates or yoga in my room if i didn’t feel like joining the activities at the hospital. I found this video and after along time of not wanting to do things I feel so much better. Thank-you.
I didn’t wanna workout today, but this workout was amazing and I’m feeling so good after doing it. Thank you so much!!
